SALMONELLOSIS - USA (06) : (NORTH CAROLINA) RESTAURANT
******************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Wed 1 Jul 2015
Source: Food Safety News [edited]
http://www.foodsafetynews.com/2015/07/at-least-30-sickened-after-dining-at-north-carolina-restaurant/#.VZVcm_ntmko


In an update posted on Wed 1 Jul 2015, the North Carolina Department of Health and Human Services stated that 248 cases of diarrheal illness and 1 death have now been identified in connection with the Tarheel Q barbecue restaurant in Lexington, NC.

The update gave the following information:
- of these 248 people, case distribution includes 19 North Carolina counties and 5 states;
- of the North Carolina cases, 72 per cent of cases are residents of Davidson County and Davie County;
- laboratory testing indicates that the BBQ sample and a sample from a patient who became ill during the beginning of the outbreak are both positive for _Salmonella_ species. The serogroup was found to be Typhimurium. Both samples have the same PFGE [pulsed-field gel electrophoresis] pattern (such as, DNA fingerprint);
- more than 50 additional clinical specimens are pending results at the state lab;
- of these 248 cases. 55 per cent are male, 41 per cent are between the ages of 20 and 49, 20 per cent have visited their provider, 13 per cent have visited the ED (emergency department), 6 per cent have been hospitalized and 1 death has been identified;
- 79 per cent of cases had illness onset dates between Tue 16 Jun 2015 and Sun 21 Jun 2015.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The number of cases in this outbreak of restaurant-associated salmonellosis has increased substantially since it was first reported. The serotype of _S. enterica_ has been identified as Typhimurium. As yet, the vehicle or vehicles involved in transmission of the pathogen is not reported.

Davie and Davidson counties in North Carolina can be seen in the central part of the state on a map at http://www.digital-topo-maps.com/county-map/north-carolina-county-map.gif. A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3489193,235. - Mod.LL]
